    "body": "### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.8.0\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, 9.0.1-700\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 12.6\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\niTerm2(Build 3.4.16), tmux 3.3a\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ntmux-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nHomebrew\n\n### How to reproduce the issue\n\nWith my [configs](https://github.com/flavono123/dotfiles/tree/master/neovim/.config/nvim)(you can install easily with `stow` following the [REAME](https://github.com/flavono123/dotfiles#installuninstall)), the colors of floating(preview) windows from fzf or mason are purple(maybe inverted?)\r\n- `,p` to open fzf window\r\n- `:Mason` to open mason UI\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nA black background like in Vim([configs](https://github.com/flavono123/dotfiles/tree/99fe67f9d4ca02422dd9c9e7c29e615ee3d05e71/vim)):\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/20619567/196147792-75c9e2cf-8511-406e-b4e0-dfd4a05b54c3.png)\r\n\n\n### Actual behavior\n\nA purple background:\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/20619567/196148014-ad96598a-bb05-4cd4-9a4a-8de77038766d.png)\r\n",
